The Alex Jones Show 
Sunday, 03 January 2010

audio files are divided on half-hour breaks
[sebaygo1]




The 2 hour Sunday show is typically a review of the past week's news and a look forward to the coming week's events.



Alex talks again with Kurt Haskell, the Michigan attorney who with his wife Lori was aboard Northwest Airlines Flight 253 and says he witnessed Umar Farouk Abdul Mutallab [accompanied by a well-dressed man] trying to board the plane in Amsterdam without a passport. Haskell compares the series of changing narratives of events with his own story, which has not changed since day one.




Alex also takes a number of calls, soliciting first-time callers.
